# Handoff file — not published on the profile
NEXT.md
NEXT--*.md

# Company-specific and third-party private material (referrers, job postings)
PRIVATE.md
apply/PRIVATE.md

# The terms the leak gate greps for. It is the denylist itself, so it cannot live in a
# tracked file — a gate that names what it forbids publishes it. Held locally; `make check`
# says out loud when it is absent rather than passing silently.
apply/ax/leakwords.txt

# Reproducible application derivatives — authored source is apply/ax/ax.org
apply/ax/build/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
events*.jsonl
# The viewer's page embeds the FULL's titles, so it is exactly as local as the FULL. A
# picture being convenient to share is not a reason to punch a hole in the boundary the
# events file keeps — what may leave is a projection, and a projection is an allowlist.
axis*.html
snapshot*.json

# Registry entries for repos the forge does not report as public
timeline/domains.local.json

# Harness-local state. The skill under .claude/skills IS published — this repo is
# public and the contract is meant to be read — but per-machine settings are not.
.claude/settings.local.json
.pi/sessions/
.pi/state/
